stabilize /ˈsteɪbɪˌlaɪz/

(stabilizing,stabilized,stabilizes) BRIT also  stabilise 

1. V-T/V-I If something stabilizes , or is stabilized , it becomes stable. 稳定 

例： Although her illness is serious, her condition is beginning to stabilize. 虽然她的病情很严重，但她的情况正开始稳定下来。 

2. stabilization N-UNCOUNT 稳定 

例： ...the stabilization of property prices. …房地产价格的稳定。

